    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold tracking-tight">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
  </section>

  <section class="prose prose-invert max-w-4xl">
    <h2>Agreement</h2>
    <p>By using TapRebook, you agree to these Terms. If you are using TapRebook on behalf of an organization, you represent that you have authority to bind that organization.</p>

    <h2>Use of service</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>You will comply with WhatsApp and BSP policies and all applicable laws.</li>
      <li>You are responsible for templates, recipients, and message content you configure.</li>
      <li>You will not misuse or attempt to disrupt the service.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Accounts &amp; billing</h2>
    <p>Paid plans are billed per order form. Fees are nonrefundable except as required by law. We may suspend service for non-payment.</p>

    <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
    <p>TapRebook owns the service and underlying IP. You own your data and content.</p>

    <h2>Data protection</h2>
    <p>Our processing of personal data is described in the <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a>. A Data Processing Addendum is available upon request.</p>

    <h2>Warranties &amp; disclaimers</h2>
    <p>The service is provided “as is”. We disclaim warranties to the extent permitted by law.</p>

    <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>To the maximum extent permitted, TapRebook is not liable for indirect or consequential damages. Aggregate liability is limited to amounts paid in the 12 months prior to the claim.</p>

    <h2>Termination</h2>
    <p>You may stop using the service at any time. We may terminate or suspend access for breach or legal reasons.</p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>We may update these Terms. Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>For questions, email <a href="mailto:legal@taprebook.com">legal@taprebook.com</a>.</p>

    <p class="text-xs opacity-80 mt-8">This sample is for guidance only and not legal advice. Consult counsel to tailor to your needs.</p>
  </section>
</Layout>


